2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a pricing rule for a single-item auction, which involves designing an algorithm to determine the optimal price. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses information-theoretic tools to analyze the performance of the proposed pricing rule. 
4. cs.EC (Economics and Computation): The paper studies the revenue maximization problem in auctions, which is a central topic in the intersection of economics and computation. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses statistical techniques to analyze the performance of the proposed pricing rule, which is a common approach in machine learning.
